Key Match Events: Trae Young led the Hawks to a 121-116 win over the Knicks
Knicks fans were overwhelmed by Hawks supporters at the State Farm Arena in Atlanta, GA
Post-Match Reflections: Trae Young made a dismissive farewell toward the exiting Knicks fans
Young said 'I hope these New York fans find their way to the exit real, real quick. Boo! Take ya'll ass home.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Knicks and Young have a dicey relationship dating back to the 2021 NBA playoffs
The Knicks will look to win in their next outing against the Milwaukee Bucks on Friday and get back at Young down the line when they next face the Hawks on Jan. 20
Others: Trae Young had 23 points, 10 assists, and six rebounds on the night
Mikal Bridges and All-Star Jalen Brunson notably underperformed with 10 points and 21 points respectively
